sudo tcpdump <options>

OPTIONS
--------

-i			:	specifies interface
-D			:	lists all interfaces available to use
-x			:	displays packet data in hex and ascii
-xx			:	same thing as -x but with ether header information
-w <file>		:	writes to a file 
-r <file>		:	reads packets from a file
-v			:	verbose
-vv			:	very verbose
port <#> -vn		:	specifies port, does not convert addresses to names, verbose
port <#> or <#> -vn	:	same as above, includes logical 'OR' for an additional port
